1
00:00:06,048 --> 00:00:09,035
Maybe they just see them as a friend.

2
00:00:09,951 --> 00:00:11,554
But I still think that
character was being an idiot.

3
00:00:11,578 --> 00:00:12,345
If it were me...

4
00:00:12,346 --> 00:00:14,547
What would you have done?

5
00:00:18,818 --> 00:00:20,487
If you knew someone liked you,

6
00:00:21,354 --> 00:00:22,522
would you confront them?

7
00:00:22,956 --> 00:00:24,858
Would you say yes, no,

8
00:00:25,392 --> 00:00:26,860
or just play dumb?

9
00:00:29,329 --> 00:00:31,131
Maybe you're right.

10
00:00:32,132 --> 00:00:33,366
My character in the script...

11
00:00:35,568 --> 00:00:36,903
Ugh, I don't know.

12
00:00:37,203 --> 00:00:37,937
He probably took A-You's kindness

13
00:00:37,938 --> 00:00:39,305
completely for granted.

14
00:00:42,742 --> 00:00:43,976
That's why

15
00:00:43,977 --> 00:00:45,711
the director left it open-ended,

16
00:00:45,712 --> 00:00:47,880
so the audience could relate

17
00:00:47,881 --> 00:00:49,241
and put themselves in those shoes.

18
00:00:50,650 --> 00:00:51,650
What about you, then?

19
00:00:53,186 --> 00:00:53,820
I'm not telling.

20
00:00:54,187 --> 00:00:55,187
Why not?

21
00:00:55,522 --> 00:00:56,555
I'm too chicken.

22
00:00:56,556 --> 00:00:57,823
Didn't you say I was too negative

23
00:00:57,824 --> 00:00:58,904
and lacked self-confidence?

24
00:01:00,660 --> 00:01:02,361
Come on, you just started out

25
00:01:02,362 --> 00:01:03,429
and you're already a hit.

26
00:01:03,430 --> 00:01:04,430
You have so many fans.

27
00:01:07,967 --> 00:01:09,302
Everyone loves you.

28
00:01:09,836 --> 00:01:11,276
Not everyone comes from a background

29
00:01:12,138 --> 00:01:13,840
that makes them feel

30
00:01:14,140 --> 00:01:15,140
safe and secure.

31
00:01:16,976 --> 00:01:18,578
I've seen your old interviews.

32
00:01:18,845 --> 00:01:20,380
You never talk about your past.

33
00:01:20,747 --> 00:01:21,981
Come on, tell me.

34
00:01:22,682 --> 00:01:23,950
Just a little bit?

35
00:01:26,586 --> 00:01:27,586
Please?

36
00:01:28,354 --> 00:01:30,089
Aren't we friends?

37
00:01:30,090 --> 00:01:31,090
Just tell me.

38
00:01:31,091 --> 00:01:32,926
I'm actually a really good listener.

39
00:01:33,193 --> 00:01:34,527
Give me something.

40
00:01:59,552 --> 00:02:00,854
See?

41
00:02:01,721 --> 00:02:03,623
This is exactly why I won't tell you.

42
00:02:04,457 --> 00:02:06,177
It took a lot for me to make this decision.

43
00:02:07,193 --> 00:02:07,861
If the time comes

44
00:02:07,862 --> 00:02:09,529
and you're crying, begging me not to go,

45
00:02:10,463 --> 00:02:11,463
what would I do?

46
00:02:12,699 --> 00:02:13,739
Don't come to the airport.

47
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:16,035
I don't want to cry in front of a crowd.

48
00:02:16,503 --> 00:02:17,036
Otherwise,

49
00:02:17,037 --> 00:02:18,917
everyone will think I'm
the one getting dumped.

50
00:02:24,010 --> 00:02:25,145
Take care of yourself.

51
00:02:27,146 --> 00:02:28,848
We both need to be okay.

52
00:02:34,521 --> 00:02:36,421
Okay, that's a wrap on this scene!

53
00:02:36,422 --> 00:02:37,789
Lunch break, everyone.

54
00:02:37,790 --> 00:02:39,324
Bai Xing's fans

55
00:02:39,325 --> 00:02:40,492
sent over some catering.

56
00:02:40,493 --> 00:02:41,493
You okay?

57
00:02:42,028 --> 00:02:43,696
Your fans are waiting for photos.

58
00:02:44,130 --> 00:02:46,010
Do you need a minute
to pull yourself together?

59
00:02:46,099 --> 00:02:48,735
It's fine. Come with me.

60
00:02:51,571 --> 00:02:52,839
But they're your fans.

61
00:02:53,406 --> 00:02:54,707
Just come with me.

62
00:02:55,575 --> 00:02:56,575
Let's go.
